<title>UK: Forward gets 129 mln stg cash offer from PCB.</title>
<headline>Forward gets 129 mln stg cash offer from PCB.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>British electronics  firm Forward Group Plc said that it had received a recommended offer from PCB Investments at 230 pence a share.</p>
<p>PCB Investments, a company owned by Hicks, Muse, Tate &amp; Furst Equity Fund III, has valued Forward at 129 million stg.  </p>
<p>PCB has already received irrevocable commitments for 22.2 million shares representing 40.3 percent of Forward's share capital.</p>
<p>The offer represents a premium of 40.2 percent over the 164p closing price of Forward on February 28.</p>
<p>The share price opened a penny higher at 165 on Monday.</p>
